results.abstract: Iran says it has launched a satellite into orbit to celebrate the 30th anniversary of the Islamic revolution, but exaggerated Iranian claims in the past have the world, and some Iranians, wondering if the news of an Iranian Sputnik is true.

results.snippet: NASA has delayed the first shuttle launching of the year by at least a week to give engineers more time to analyze potential problems with valves that keep fuel flowing in the Discovery's main engines, an official said. The shuttle had been scheduled...
results.lead_paragraph: NASA has delayed the first shuttle launching of the year by at least a week to give engineers more time to analyze potential problems with valves that keep fuel flowing in the Discovery's main engines, an official said. The shuttle had been scheduled for launching on Feb. 12 on a mission to the International Space Station, to deliver the station's last solar-power wing and drop off a Japanese astronaut who is joining the crew. (REUTERS)

headline.main: Debris Spews Into Space In Collision Of Satellites

results.snippet: Debris from the crash of an American and a Russian satellite could pose a threat to the space station.

byline.original: By WILLIAM J. BROAD; William Harwood contributed reporting

results.lead_paragraph: For decades, space experts have warned of orbits around the planet growing so crowded that two satellites might one day slam into one another, producing swarms of treacherous debris. It happened Tuesday. And the whirling fragments could pose a threat to the International Space Station, orbiting 215 miles up with three astronauts on board, though officials said the risk was now small.

headline.main: Ben Blank, TV Innovator, Dies at 87

results.snippet: Mr. Blank introduced the concept of using logolike images behind anchors as signatures for major news coverage.
results.lead_paragraph: Ben Blank, who as graphics director for CBS and later ABC television news introduced the concept of using logolike images behind anchors as signatures for major news coverage, died on Feb. 3 at his home in Teaneck, N.J. He was 87. The cause was complications of a stroke suffered three years ago, said his daughter Karen Blank.

results.abstract: Traveling with an entourage at the Vanity Fair party is generally frowned upon, but Penelope Cruz happened to be related to most of her gang and they all entered the party at the Sunset Towers wearing P's on their foreheads, leaving no doubt as to their affiliation. That's just how they roll.
